qas.question: What is Catalan the derivitive of?
What is the Latin for Calalunya?
Where did the Catalan  people originate?
What is the root word from which Catalonia comes?

context: The word Catalan derives from the territory of Catalonia, itself of disputed etymology. The main theory suggests that Catalunya (Latin <a1_0>Gathia Launia<a1_0/>) derives from the name <a3_0>Gothia<a3_0/> or Gauthia ("Land of the Goths"), since the origins of the Catalan counts, lords and people were found in the <a2_0>March of Gothia<a2_0/>, whence Gothland > Gothlandia > Gothalania > <a0_0>Catalonia<a0_0/> theoretically derived.
